            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">The King laughed: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">“If I obtain to escape, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">what about the later men?” ??? </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">He answered: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">“I do not know about it. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">[Later] The mighty king Ping ordered prince Mu to go to Cheng Fu. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">He passed past Shen, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">cooked food at Sheng Kui. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">The duke of the [Sheng Kui] city, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">Han met him kneeling in the midst of the (hemp) fields. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">The king asked the duke of the city: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">“What is this?”. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">The duke of the city answered: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">“a hemp field.” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">The Prince asked: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">“What do you do with hemp fields?” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">He said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en">“To grow hemp.” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en">The prince asked: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en">“What do you do with hemp?” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en">He answered: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-3a.12" xml:lang="en">“We make clothes with it.” </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">The duke rose up and said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">“I am now going to report </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">that when the former lord [king Zhuang of Chu] had reached the area of the Huai river, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">he cooked food at Sheng Kui. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">The plate of pickled sauce was not cooked in the oven, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en">and the king said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en">“the XX sauce should not be covered.” </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">The former lord knew that the XX sauce should not be covered </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">and the plate of pickled sauce is not cooked in the oven [he mastered even the minutiae of the people’s livelihood], </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">[but] as the prince does not [even] know about hemp, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">the prince will not obtain to rule the state of Chu, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0064_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">and most likely will not obtain [even] to rule the state of Chu as a minister. </seg>
                </p>

